main event: Multiple unidentified aerial objects were observed and photographed by US naval crews over Guantanamo Bay, Cuba on April 4, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were described as metallic, circular in shape, and approximately 30-40 feet in diameter.
The objects were observed maneuvering at high speeds, making sharp turns, and appearing to hover.
The sightings occurred over a period of approximately 2 hours, between 0200 and 0400 hours.
No sound was heard from the objects.
The photographs and associated documentation were forwarded to Project Blue Book for further analysis and evaluation.
sighted object: metallic, circular objects approximately 30-40 feet in diameter
